Global Red Quinoa Market Insights
Red Quinoa Market size was valued at USD 0.8 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 1.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Red Quinoa Market Overview
The global red quinoa market is projected to grow significantly in the coming years, driven by increasing consumer awareness about healthy eating, the growing popularity of plant-based proteins, and the nutritional benefits of red quinoa. As of 2024, the market is valued at approximately USD 1.2 billion and is expected to expand at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030. Red quinoa is recognized for its high fiber content, rich protein profile, and various vitamins and minerals, making it a preferred choice among health-conscious consumers. As more people shift to gluten-free and plant-based diets, the demand for quinoa, especially red quinoa, continues to rise in both developed and emerging markets.

